1
00:00:54,654 --> 00:00:59,489
In the middle of Huntington,
West Virginia, there is a river.

2
00:01:03,897 --> 00:01:06,991
Next to this river, there is a steel mill.

3
00:01:11,738 --> 00:01:14,866
And next to the steel mill,
there is a school.

4
00:01:20,246 --> 00:01:23,511
In the middle of this school,
there is a fountain.

5
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:31,414
Each year, on the exact same day,
at the exact same hour...

6
00:01:31,591 --> 00:01:34,424
...the water to this fountain is turned off.

7
00:01:35,762 --> 00:01:39,027
And in this moment, once every year...

8
00:01:40,133 --> 00:01:44,194
...throughout the town,
throughout the school...

9
00:01:45,405 --> 00:01:47,771
...time stands still.

10
00:02:04,958 --> 00:02:07,984
Chris Griffen with a reception.
That is a first down.

11
00:02:08,161 --> 00:02:13,224
But Marshall is all out of time-outs,
and the clock is now ticking.

12
00:02:13,399 --> 00:02:16,562
If they wanna get another play off,
the Herd had better hurry.

13
00:02:17,570 --> 00:02:20,368
Call it in, Red! Call it in!

14
00:02:23,510 --> 00:02:27,810
- Griffen! Okay, Chris Griffen! Hustle up!
- I'm good, I'm good.

15
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:29,710
The Herd looks a little disorganized.

16
00:02:29,883 --> 00:02:34,081
They're looking for a play from the sideline,
and they are almost out of time.

17
00:02:34,254 --> 00:02:37,382
We are talking about seconds.
Marshall needs to get down and over...

18
00:02:37,557 --> 00:02:39,548
- 77-Victory. Go! Go, go, go!
- Yes, sir.

19
00:02:39,726 --> 00:02:41,557
77-Victory. You're out.

20
00:02:42,362 --> 00:02:46,423
V, 77! V, 77!

21
00:02:52,305 --> 00:02:53,932
Come on! Snap the ball!

22
00:02:54,807 --> 00:02:56,297
Set!

23
00:02:57,010 --> 00:03:01,003
Snap it! Snap it! Snap it!

24
00:03:01,915 --> 00:03:03,382
Come on!

25
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:05,547
Hut!

26
00:03:14,527 --> 00:03:17,223
Strong side! He's open!

27
00:03:17,397 --> 00:03:19,763
He's open! Throw!

28
00:03:34,047 --> 00:03:36,777
And that'll be it for the Herd.

29
00:03:38,084 --> 00:03:40,314
That's right, the clock has hit all zeroes...

30
00:03:40,486 --> 00:03:43,546
...and the Carolina faithful
are already on their feet.

31
00:03:43,723 --> 00:03:44,951
So there you have it.

32
00:03:45,124 --> 00:03:46,887
- It's all over, folks.
- Good game, Red.

33
00:03:47,060 --> 00:03:51,554
Marshall loses a tough one,
17-14 to the East Carolina Pirates.

34
00:03:51,731 --> 00:03:53,562
Red's got his work cut out for him.

35
00:03:53,733 --> 00:03:57,965
Well, there goes my weekend.
Red'll be in the film room till Monday.

36
00:03:58,137 --> 00:03:59,434
He'd better.

37
00:03:59,606 --> 00:04:02,404
Your husband hasn't figured out
how to beat the 3-4 all year.

38
00:04:02,575 --> 00:04:04,907
Co-captain Nate Ruffin
and cornerback Tom Bogdan...

39
00:04:05,078 --> 00:04:08,639
...are two of four starters who were
left back in Huntington due to injuries.

40
00:04:08,815 --> 00:04:12,683
Surprised to see you. Figured the chairman
of the school board would be at the game.

41
00:04:12,852 --> 00:04:15,047
This place won't run itself,
you know that.

42
00:04:15,221 --> 00:04:17,951
- Furnace ready for the tap?
- Yeah.

43
00:04:20,793 --> 00:04:23,489
The next week is a must-win.

44
00:04:23,663 --> 00:04:25,460
They're all must-wins, Gene.

45
00:04:25,632 --> 00:04:29,728
No word yet on whether any or all of the
injured players will be available next...

46
00:04:34,641 --> 00:04:37,804
Hey, Sandy, can I get
some more foil in here?

47
00:04:38,678 --> 00:04:42,944
The score, 17-14, East Carolina Pirates.
Quarterback Teddy Shoebridge...

48
00:04:43,116 --> 00:04:44,583
I got it!

49
00:04:49,322 --> 00:04:53,315
Hey, where's the flag?
Where's the flag? Flag on...

50
00:04:53,493 --> 00:04:57,020
Fifty-five! Blocking in the...

51
00:04:57,196 --> 00:05:00,097
...if that confusion on the Marshall sideline
at the end of the game...

52
00:05:00,266 --> 00:05:04,202
...won't make that target on
Coach Tolley's back a little bit bigger.

53
00:05:04,370 --> 00:05:08,238
I'm not gonna ask you guys again.
Dinner's ready.

54
00:05:09,809 --> 00:05:11,640
That means you too, Keith.

55
00:05:11,811 --> 00:05:14,609
Please, just a few more seconds?
Dad's not off yet.

56
00:05:14,781 --> 00:05:17,944
He'll still be droning on about that game
when he gets home tonight.

57
00:05:18,117 --> 00:05:20,176
Get out from under there,
Keith Morehouse.

58
00:05:20,353 --> 00:05:24,881
I'm Gene Morehouse saying
good night, and go Herd!

59
00:05:25,158 --> 00:05:26,455
Fellas...

60
00:05:28,027 --> 00:05:30,393
...you gave a good effort out there today.

61
00:05:33,066 --> 00:05:35,193
But let me be clear about this:

62
00:05:35,601 --> 00:05:39,093
A good effort is not enough.

63
00:05:42,842 --> 00:05:44,707
Now, I'm proud of you.

64
00:05:46,479 --> 00:05:49,141
But I will not accept losing with you.

65
00:05:49,749 --> 00:05:52,081
Because there's only one thing
they judge us on.

66
00:05:52,251 --> 00:05:54,981
There's only one thing people remember.

67
00:05:56,022 --> 00:05:58,684
And it ain't how we play the game!

68
00:06:02,762 --> 00:06:04,354
Winning...

69
00:06:05,398 --> 00:06:07,025
...is everything.

70
00:06:11,003 --> 00:06:12,368
Plane leaves in an hour.

71
00:06:13,139 --> 00:06:15,198
We'll be home by 8.

72
00:06:15,375 --> 00:06:19,539
Plenty of time for y'all to do whatever
the hell y'all do on a Saturday night.

73
00:06:24,317 --> 00:06:27,286
Now, see, Bogdan, the reason we lost
is because we weren't there.

74
00:06:27,453 --> 00:06:31,321
Chocolate Thunder, White Lightning? We the
best defensive players in the conference.

75
00:06:31,491 --> 00:06:32,856
I'm Chocolate Thunder, right?

76
00:06:33,025 --> 00:06:35,721
Why you so scared to introduce me
to your girlfriend, then?

77
00:06:35,895 --> 00:06:37,920
Listen, stop being so
overconfident, Ruffin.

78
00:06:38,097 --> 00:06:41,863
All right, Rock, Paper, Scissors for tickets.
Let's go, right now.

79
00:06:44,103 --> 00:06:45,593
It's okay. I'll get the popcorn.

80
00:06:45,772 --> 00:06:47,433
East Carolina?

81
00:06:47,607 --> 00:06:50,440
I mean, I can understand giving up
300 yards to Bowling Green.

82
00:06:50,610 --> 00:06:51,941
But East Carolina?

83
00:06:52,111 --> 00:06:55,137
Well, you can't do nothing
about injuries, you know?

84
00:06:55,715 --> 00:06:57,706
What happened? Is it broken?

85
00:06:57,884 --> 00:06:59,784
It's dislocated.

86
00:06:59,952 --> 00:07:01,943
What's wrong with you, Tom?

87
00:07:02,922 --> 00:07:04,822
Come on, man. Gonna miss the previews.

88
00:07:04,991 --> 00:07:09,223
Nineteen carries, 108 yards, Paul,
your boy Chris played a hell of a game.

89
00:07:09,395 --> 00:07:11,863
I'd have taken the win any day.
Isn't that right, Don?

90
00:07:12,031 --> 00:07:14,056
What, now, we didn't win?

91
00:07:15,435 --> 00:07:18,404
You of all people, Don.
If you're not gonna listen to the game...

92
00:07:18,571 --> 00:07:21,165
...you gotta know the result
so you can pretend you did.

93
00:07:21,340 --> 00:07:23,535
- Well, I'm doing my best, Paul.
- You hungry?

94
00:07:23,709 --> 00:07:25,643
No, thank you. I'm all set.

95
00:07:25,812 --> 00:07:28,645
Lloyd? Usual for me tonight,
just more of it. I'm starving.

96
00:07:28,815 --> 00:07:30,874
- You got it.
- Go ahead, excuse me.

97
00:07:31,050 --> 00:07:34,042
Well, the board has asked me
to run a few ideas through you...

98
00:07:34,220 --> 00:07:38,281
...about some potential improvements
to the university's physical plant.

99
00:07:48,634 --> 00:07:50,363
There's Chris!

100
00:07:53,773 --> 00:07:57,174
What took you so long to call?
Tell Joe he can't run it to the inside...

101
00:07:57,343 --> 00:07:59,971
Slow down, Reggie. Just listen.

102
00:08:00,146 --> 00:08:03,946
- I just need a favor, not your life story.
- What you need?

103
00:08:04,116 --> 00:08:08,985
I need you to go get us a case
of Falls City Beer. Falls City.

104
00:08:09,155 --> 00:08:12,750
- Go to the liquor store on Fourth. Yeah.
- Fourth Street?

105
00:08:12,925 --> 00:08:15,519
- Hey, are the guys with you?
- Yeah, Reggie.

106
00:08:15,695 --> 00:08:17,686
What is it, godd...?

107
00:08:18,364 --> 00:08:21,800
That's right, Reggie. You carry the two
and you divide by the sum...

108
00:08:21,968 --> 00:08:25,460
Yeah, math class is over.
Let's get on the plane. Come on.

109
00:08:28,241 --> 00:08:31,039
- I'll see you in a couple of hours, right?
- You know you are.

110
00:08:31,210 --> 00:08:33,337
- I'm gonna stay at my dad's house tonight.
- No.

111
00:08:33,513 --> 00:08:36,209
He's gonna wanna go over his
post-game breakdown.

112
00:08:36,649 --> 00:08:39,015
Sorry. We've been doing it
since I was a kid.

113
00:08:39,185 --> 00:08:41,346
You gonna tell him about California, right?

114
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:45,355
Are you kidding? After a loss?
We want him in a good mood.

115
00:08:45,525 --> 00:08:47,117
Yeah.

116
00:08:47,393 --> 00:08:50,157
Don't worry. I will.

117
00:08:52,198 --> 00:08:54,166
Just not this weekend.

118
00:08:54,333 --> 00:08:56,460
Griffen! Let's go!

119
00:08:57,436 --> 00:08:59,427
I love you, Chris Griffen.

120
00:09:00,506 --> 00:09:02,497
Come on, Annie!

121
00:09:04,410 --> 00:09:06,844
- Race you back.
- Let's go! Hurry up!

122
00:09:07,013 --> 00:09:08,913
I'm coming!

123
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:16,249
What's this concert you're missing?

124
00:09:16,422 --> 00:09:20,415
It's just my granddaughter's piano recital.
Man, she sure is cute when she does that.

125
00:09:20,593 --> 00:09:23,391
That's the crap I missed
first time around with my boys.

126
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:24,996
Now they got kids of their own.

127
00:09:25,164 --> 00:09:28,224
Anyway, got a long ride ahead of me.
Have a great flight.

128
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:30,995
Hutch, tell you what,
I'll do the recruiting trip.

129
00:09:31,170 --> 00:09:35,607
You go home and see your granddaughter's
recital. I'm gonna do it. I'm doing it.

130
00:09:37,910 --> 00:09:40,743
- Thanks, Red. All right.
- I'll see you on Monday morning.

131
00:09:42,582 --> 00:09:44,447
Good man, Red.

132
00:09:45,318 --> 00:09:47,684
You can grab me a beer back home.

133
00:09:57,463 --> 00:10:00,591
Because if he keeps on pulling
and no money comes out...

134
00:10:00,766 --> 00:10:02,358
- Good evening.
- Doris.

135
00:10:02,535 --> 00:10:05,436
It's Red Dawson, calling from Greenville.

136
00:10:06,472 --> 00:10:09,373
Could I trouble you to look and see
if Carole's home next door?

137
00:10:12,178 --> 00:10:13,611
Sure doesn't look like it, Red.

138
00:10:13,779 --> 00:10:16,646
Could you do me a big favor
and leave her a message for me?

139
00:10:16,816 --> 00:10:20,183
Tell her that I gotta drive to Virginia
tonight on a recruiting trip...

140
00:10:20,353 --> 00:10:22,378
...and I'm not gonna be home
till tomorrow.

141
00:10:22,555 --> 00:10:24,716
- Got it.
- All right, you have a good night, now.

142
00:10:24,890 --> 00:10:27,415
- All right, bye.
- Night, Red.

143
00:10:45,011 --> 00:10:48,572
- You thinking about that girlfriend of yours?
- Yeah, coach.

144
00:10:50,016 --> 00:10:51,677
Nice job, son.

145
00:10:53,019 --> 00:10:54,816
Hey, that was a big hit today. Big hit.

146
00:10:54,987 --> 00:10:57,080
I would've caught that pass
if I had my cross.

147
00:10:57,256 --> 00:10:58,484
What'd you do with it?

148
00:10:58,658 --> 00:11:02,116
You would've caught it if you had good
hands. Ain't that right, Shoebridge?

149
00:11:02,294 --> 00:11:07,163
Hey, Gene, this is gonna sound a little
weird, but I need you to do me a favor.

150
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:10,530
Want you to scratch my back.
That target on there is starting to itch.

151
00:11:10,703 --> 00:11:13,035
You can't believe everything
you hear on the radio.

152
00:11:13,205 --> 00:11:15,105
Oh, yeah, I can.

153
00:11:18,577 --> 00:11:23,344
All right, boys, let's sit up straight.
Tighten those ties, fix those collars.

154
00:11:23,516 --> 00:11:25,450
- We are?
- Marshall!

155
00:11:26,252 --> 00:11:27,719
Almost home.

156
00:11:30,222 --> 00:11:32,452
This is Captain Dettro speaking.

157
00:11:32,625 --> 00:11:35,287
Looks like we made good time
in spite of the weather...

158
00:11:35,461 --> 00:11:40,262
...so if everyone could return to their
seats now, we'll be landing shortly.

159
00:12:09,729 --> 00:12:11,526
Fill her up for you?

160
00:12:11,764 --> 00:12:13,129
Yes, sir.

161
00:12:18,871 --> 00:12:20,600
These peanuts look good.

162
00:12:22,274 --> 00:12:24,208
I'll get a bunch of them too.

163
00:12:24,376 --> 00:12:27,504
Sure. They're just 50 cents.
Help yourself.

164
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:30,649
Regular's on the left,
Cajun's on the right.

165
00:12:30,816 --> 00:12:33,080
Incredibly, there has been
another plane crash...

166
00:12:33,252 --> 00:12:34,981
How spicy are these Cajun...?

167
00:12:35,154 --> 00:12:38,385
...in moderate rain and fog
in West Virginia.

168
00:12:38,557 --> 00:12:40,286
What did he just say?

169
00:12:40,459 --> 00:12:42,324
- Wait. Turn that up.
- No, what happened...

170
00:12:42,495 --> 00:12:43,723
What did that say?

171
00:12:43,896 --> 00:12:47,457
Early reports do not indicate
the condition of those aboard.

172
00:12:54,140 --> 00:12:55,437
Excuse me, everybody...

173
00:12:55,608 --> 00:12:57,007
Annette said you look funny
when you're getting dressed.

174
00:13:02,615 --> 00:13:04,708
Bye, Carole.
Say hello to your husband for me.

175
00:13:04,884 --> 00:13:07,717
- This is Lloyd.
- See you, Lloyd!

176
00:13:15,594 --> 00:13:17,152
What's happened?

177
00:13:29,742 --> 00:13:31,437
Hey!

178
00:13:34,180 --> 00:13:36,876
- Hey, you going to the airport?
- Yeah, get in.

179
00:13:37,049 --> 00:13:40,917
All right. I'm getting in. Hold on.
All right, good.

180
00:13:59,905 --> 00:14:02,135
- Hey, did they say anything?
- Hey, come on!

181
00:14:02,308 --> 00:14:05,766
No one's going in there.
I can't let you up there.

182
00:14:05,945 --> 00:14:07,970
- Get that truck up the hill!
- Come on!

183
00:14:08,147 --> 00:14:09,546
Hey, Randy!

184
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:13,109
Come on, keep going, come on.

185
00:14:17,756 --> 00:14:19,451
Hey, watch the hose!

186
00:14:31,337 --> 00:14:34,568
Got the president of the university here!

187
00:14:36,442 --> 00:14:38,433
Oh, my God in heaven.

188
00:14:39,511 --> 00:14:41,536
Oh, my God.

189
00:14:46,952 --> 00:14:48,613
Come on.

190
00:14:50,155 --> 00:14:51,850
Let's go.

191
00:14:53,158 --> 00:14:56,184
- Hey, get behind the ropes!
- Just tell us the name of the airline!

192
00:14:56,362 --> 00:14:59,729
- If I knew anything, I'd tell you!
- Just look at the front of the plane!

193
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:02,925
Son, there is no
front of the plane anymore.

194
00:15:06,538 --> 00:15:07,903
Bring another hose down here!

195
00:15:08,073 --> 00:15:10,837
No, stay back. Stay up there! No!

196
00:15:11,010 --> 00:15:14,002
- Let's go!
- Nate! Nate Ruffin!

197
00:15:14,947 --> 00:15:18,576
This our boys' plane?
This our boys' plane?!

198
00:16:48,774 --> 00:16:50,674
It's so terrible.

199
00:17:39,024 --> 00:17:40,252
You didn't get my message?

200
00:18:00,712 --> 00:18:04,170
Marshall University in West Virginia
is in a state of shock today...

201
00:18:04,349 --> 00:18:08,877
...following the terrible tragedy of last
Saturday night's crash of a chartered airline.

202
00:18:09,054 --> 00:18:11,181
Seventy-five people died in the wreckage.

203
00:18:11,356 --> 00:18:13,085
The football team, the coaches...

204
00:18:13,258 --> 00:18:16,421
...and some prominent residents
traveling with the team...

205
00:18:47,526 --> 00:18:49,687
These were beautiful young men...

206
00:18:49,862 --> 00:18:55,061
...and it's just a tragedy
that is beyond all comprehension.

207
00:19:24,429 --> 00:19:28,866
No one of us will ever
enter this stadium...

208
00:19:29,034 --> 00:19:32,060
...without thoughts of them.

209
00:19:32,971 --> 00:19:39,206
And so, our Lord, grant them
eternal rest and peace...

210
00:19:39,478 --> 00:19:42,641
...which enables them
at this very moment...

211
00:19:42,814 --> 00:19:48,411
...to look upon us here
and smile and be with us.

212
00:19:48,587 --> 00:19:53,320
This is our faith, this is our hope.

213
00:19:54,459 --> 00:19:56,086
Amen.

214
00:20:27,025 --> 00:20:29,459
Those were not welcome days.

215
00:20:30,862 --> 00:20:32,762
We buried sons...

216
00:20:32,965 --> 00:20:34,626
...brothers...

217
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,267
...mothers...

218
00:20:36,435 --> 00:20:38,528
...fathers...

219
00:20:39,304 --> 00:20:40,794
...fiancés.

220
00:20:48,614 --> 00:20:52,675
Clocks ticked, but time did not pass.

221
00:21:00,292 --> 00:21:03,523
The sun rose and the sun set.

222
00:21:05,197 --> 00:21:07,665
But the shadows remained.

223
00:21:11,803 --> 00:21:13,532
When once there was sound...

224
00:21:15,140 --> 00:21:17,608
...now there was silence.

225
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:30,220
What once was whole...

226
00:21:31,223 --> 00:21:33,623
...now is shattered.

227
00:22:02,187 --> 00:22:04,849
Have you mentioned this
to any of the other board members?

228
00:22:05,023 --> 00:22:09,016
A few. Most of them
would prefer not to think about it.

229
00:22:09,194 --> 00:22:12,254
I can understand that sentiment.

230
00:22:12,431 --> 00:22:16,128
It doesn't make sense to rush
right back into it, you know?

231
00:22:16,301 --> 00:22:19,634
Our coaching staff, gone.
Our athletic department, gone.

232
00:22:19,805 --> 00:22:22,968
So many of our boosters, gone.

233
00:22:23,141 --> 00:22:25,666
We'd have to start
all over again from scratch.

234
00:22:25,844 --> 00:22:30,042
My God, we don't have the resources
or the manpower right now.

235
00:22:30,215 --> 00:22:33,184
I know all the reasons
to suspend the program, Paul.

236
00:22:33,352 --> 00:22:35,479
I'm just surprised to hear it
coming from you.

237
00:22:35,654 --> 00:22:37,815
This town just didn't lose
a football team, Don.

238
00:22:37,989 --> 00:22:41,618
We lost doctors, lawyers,
city councilmen.

239
00:22:41,793 --> 00:22:44,284
We lost fathers, sons, husbands.

240
