so I guess it's just three.

485
00:41:08,499 --> 00:41:09,830
Okay.

486
00:41:11,035 --> 00:41:13,765
I'm Coach Jack Lengyel, guys.

487
00:41:14,071 --> 00:41:16,471
Normally, I'm bad with names,
so the good news is...

488
00:41:16,640 --> 00:41:19,507
...I may actually be able
to keep you fellas straight.

489
00:41:20,044 --> 00:41:21,944
Nate, is it?

490
00:41:22,112 --> 00:41:25,377
Okay, now, hold on
while I commit this to memory. Nate.

491
00:41:25,850 --> 00:41:27,841
As in Nate the Great.

492
00:41:28,018 --> 00:41:30,748
Date, late, escape. Wait. Nate.

493
00:41:30,921 --> 00:41:32,684
McDrake.

494
00:41:32,857 --> 00:41:37,191
I got it. Locked.
Kid I went to grade school with.

495
00:41:37,361 --> 00:41:40,853
See, that's a little word-association trick
I learned. Helps jog the recall.

496
00:41:41,031 --> 00:41:44,228
I read about it in Redbook.
And I tell you what, it really works, too.

497
00:41:45,469 --> 00:41:48,029
Well, we're in this together now, boys.

498
00:41:49,173 --> 00:41:51,971
I'm not going anywhere,
and that's a promise.

499
00:41:52,810 --> 00:41:54,072
Already got one name down.

500
00:41:55,212 --> 00:41:57,612
Soon as the wife gets things
settled at the house...

501
00:41:57,781 --> 00:42:01,217
...y'all are coming over for supper,
and I'll get the other two.

502
00:42:03,020 --> 00:42:05,181
We are Marshall.

503
00:42:07,992 --> 00:42:09,857
It's a new day, men.

504
00:42:11,896 --> 00:42:14,729
I like those boys, Don. I do. I do.

505
00:42:14,899 --> 00:42:17,367
The thing is, I'm gonna need
55 more just like them.

506
00:42:17,535 --> 00:42:20,504
Oh, that I can't help you with, I'm afraid.

507
00:42:20,738 --> 00:42:22,831
Well, actually, you can, Don.

508
00:42:23,941 --> 00:42:28,537
You see, I need you to petition
the NCAA for me.

509
00:42:28,712 --> 00:42:33,342
Ask them to make an exception.
Allow us to play freshmen.

510
00:42:33,517 --> 00:42:36,577
Now, it's the only chance we have
to get any edge on recruiting...

511
00:42:36,754 --> 00:42:39,450
...much less put a full football team
on the field.

512
00:42:39,623 --> 00:42:41,853
I mean, we are way behind here.

513
00:42:42,026 --> 00:42:46,190
Well, you know the NCAA
better than I do, Jack.

514
00:42:46,363 --> 00:42:50,094
They're rigid as a board.
They don't make exceptions.

515
00:42:51,468 --> 00:42:52,935
Usually true.

516
00:42:53,771 --> 00:42:55,102
Yeah.

517
00:42:56,473 --> 00:43:01,410
Hey, you know, my son, he crapped
his pants yesterday. Now, he's 4.

518
00:43:01,579 --> 00:43:04,946
All right, now, my wife is out shopping,
so I had to clean him up.

519
00:43:05,783 --> 00:43:08,217
She got home. I told her what happened.
She says, "I can't believe it."

520
00:43:08,385 --> 00:43:11,149
I said, "I can't believe it either.
The kid's 4 years old...

521
00:43:11,322 --> 00:43:13,586
...he shouldn't be doing that shit."
Pun intended.

522
00:43:13,757 --> 00:43:16,555
You know what she says to me?
She says, "Jack, no, not that.

523
00:43:17,161 --> 00:43:20,597
I can't believe you finally
changed a diaper."

524
00:43:22,466 --> 00:43:24,491
What are you talking about?

525
00:43:25,302 --> 00:43:27,600
There's a first time for everything.

526
00:43:31,342 --> 00:43:32,741
Hey, I know you.

527
00:43:32,910 --> 00:43:35,208
In the middle. Yes, I do.

528
00:43:35,379 --> 00:43:39,110
Ask me your name. Go ahead,
I won't even look. Ask me your name.

529
00:43:40,150 --> 00:43:43,347
- What's my name?
- Nate Ruffin.

530
00:43:43,520 --> 00:43:47,115
Team co-captain. Eleven interceptions
in only seven games last year.

531
00:43:49,927 --> 00:43:51,485
Redbook.

532
00:43:51,996 --> 00:43:53,486
Stuff really works.

533
00:43:53,664 --> 00:43:55,825
Hey, we can do this, doc.

534
00:44:02,873 --> 00:44:06,468
What are those, 1-by-5s?

535
00:44:06,644 --> 00:44:07,872
One-by-sixes.

536
00:44:09,580 --> 00:44:12,413
They don't look that wide from down here.

537
00:44:15,619 --> 00:44:19,020
- Saw you guys play once.
- Did we win?

538
00:44:19,957 --> 00:44:21,982
It was the Ashland game.

539
00:44:22,292 --> 00:44:23,691
Well, that'd be a no, then.

540
00:44:24,862 --> 00:44:27,990
Well, you guys looked pretty good
till the fourth quarter.

541
00:44:29,133 --> 00:44:31,397
Probably should've gone to the nickel.

542
00:44:33,370 --> 00:44:35,497
You know, you're probably right.

543
00:44:35,673 --> 00:44:38,198
You know, I appreciate you
coming out here to see me...

544
00:44:38,375 --> 00:44:42,971
...but they already came out here to ask me
back and I already told them that I'm not...

545
00:44:44,481 --> 00:44:47,575
- ...coming back, so...
- Yeah, I heard. I heard about that.

546
00:44:49,319 --> 00:44:53,085
Just thought I could make you
a better offer.

547
00:44:53,557 --> 00:44:56,321
You know, they asked you
to be the head coach.

548
00:44:57,227 --> 00:44:59,161
I want you to be the assistant coach.

549
00:45:01,198 --> 00:45:03,257
I think that's a demotion, Jack.

550
00:45:03,434 --> 00:45:04,958
Well, maybe.

551
00:45:05,402 --> 00:45:06,869
Maybe not.

552
00:45:07,037 --> 00:45:11,235
I mean, it's the same duties,
practically, just less pay.

553
00:45:12,543 --> 00:45:15,706
Same hours. Less responsibility.

554
00:45:15,879 --> 00:45:18,006
Same team, less pressure.

555
00:45:19,383 --> 00:45:24,252
I tell you, Red, you know,
the cupboard is pretty bare.

556
00:45:24,421 --> 00:45:28,551
And I could use some recruiting help
from someone who knows the area.

557
00:45:35,432 --> 00:45:38,458
You know, Carole and I
moved here two years ago. It was...

558
00:45:39,937 --> 00:45:41,905
...spring of '69.

559
00:45:44,208 --> 00:45:46,108
They had hired me as a receivers coach...

560
00:45:46,276 --> 00:45:50,076
...but when I got here, they told me
I was in charge of recruiting too, so...

561
00:45:50,981 --> 00:45:55,611
That first year I went out
and I got us 20 kids.

562
00:45:56,253 --> 00:46:00,917
Went to 20 homes.
Sat in 20 living rooms.

563
00:46:02,159 --> 00:46:05,890
And I promised 20 mothers
that I'd look after their sons.

564
00:46:07,898 --> 00:46:10,423
It'd have been the class of '73.

565
00:46:14,638 --> 00:46:16,936
There's not one of them left.

566
00:46:20,944 --> 00:46:23,071
So let me ask you, Jack:

567
00:46:24,481 --> 00:46:28,975
How am I supposed to look a mother in the
eye and promise her anything ever again?

568
00:46:35,292 --> 00:46:37,317
I don't know, Red.

569
00:46:45,335 --> 00:46:48,600
I just don't think I could
take that field again, Jack.

570
00:47:00,617 --> 00:47:04,053
Is that the Ohio Valley Coal line?

571
00:47:04,221 --> 00:47:07,122
The same one that went off the tracks
near Akron last winter?

572
00:47:07,291 --> 00:47:10,317
Yep. That's the one.

573
00:47:11,195 --> 00:47:13,095
Back on track.

574
00:47:18,502 --> 00:47:22,029
Well, listen,
if you're able to figure it out...

575
00:47:22,206 --> 00:47:24,970
...door's always open.
It was a pleasure meeting you, Red.

576
00:47:25,142 --> 00:47:27,110
Nice meeting you.

577
00:47:27,277 --> 00:47:31,145
I'll keep that defensive-nickel
package idea in mind...

578
00:47:31,315 --> 00:47:35,513
...for my fourth quarters in the future.
Maybe get a few more W's.

579
00:47:37,321 --> 00:47:38,913
One-by-six, huh?

580
00:47:39,089 --> 00:47:40,317
Yup.

581
00:47:40,490 --> 00:47:43,857
Same coverage, less boards.

582
00:47:48,065 --> 00:47:49,396
Hey, Tom.

583
00:47:52,069 --> 00:47:54,094
Guess we got us a coach, huh?

584
00:48:03,347 --> 00:48:04,871
Hey, look.

585
00:48:06,283 --> 00:48:10,686
When they first roomed us together
freshman year, I wasn't too sure about you.

586
00:48:11,855 --> 00:48:15,951
You know? But we stuck it out,
and now you're my best friend.

587
00:48:17,261 --> 00:48:19,627
I mean, remember freshman two-a-days?

588
00:48:19,796 --> 00:48:23,698
I'm puking my guts out and
I wanna quit football and you won't let me?

589
00:48:25,135 --> 00:48:27,729
Now, you never gave up on us
out there on the field...

590
00:48:27,905 --> 00:48:30,396
...and I'm not gonna give up on you now.

591
00:48:34,378 --> 00:48:36,039
Tom, man.

592
00:48:36,213 --> 00:48:41,947
It's our team. Now, they left this to us.
It's up to us! It's on our shoulders, man.

593
00:48:43,487 --> 00:48:45,785
I need you with me, Tom.

594
00:48:45,956 --> 00:48:48,220
I should've been with them, Nate.

595
00:48:48,392 --> 00:48:52,590
- Look, Tom, I understand, and I feel...
- No, you don't! You don't, Nate! You don't.

596
00:48:54,898 --> 00:48:57,162
What you talking about?

597
00:48:59,369 --> 00:49:01,337
I overslept.

598
00:49:02,239 --> 00:49:05,265
That's why I wasn't on the plane, Nate.
I overslept.

599
00:49:05,943 --> 00:49:08,810
I wasn't hurt or sick.
And I should've been there.

600
00:49:08,979 --> 00:49:11,004
I should have been with them!

601
00:49:12,783 --> 00:49:16,844
I'm sorry. I just can't play football
right now. Okay? It's not in me.

602
00:49:19,389 --> 00:49:22,586
I can't do it, you understand that, right?
Look at me.

603
00:49:25,362 --> 00:49:26,989
I'm sorry.

604
00:49:27,364 --> 00:49:29,025
Tom.

605
00:49:46,950 --> 00:49:49,316
Thought you might like some dessert.

606
00:49:50,787 --> 00:49:52,687
Thank you, Annie.

607
00:49:53,890 --> 00:49:55,551
I'm gonna get you some silverware.

608
00:50:57,821 --> 00:50:59,311
Yup.

609
00:51:00,290 --> 00:51:01,621
Game day.

610
00:51:07,898 --> 00:51:09,297
Yup.

611
00:51:18,442 --> 00:51:23,607
So I'll give you one year.

612
00:51:26,183 --> 00:51:29,584
Well, if that's all the time we've got,
we'd better get started.

613
00:51:42,532 --> 00:51:44,090
Coach Mickey Jackson.

614
00:51:46,736 --> 00:51:48,533
Coach McNally.

615
00:51:52,075 --> 00:51:53,599
Coach Riley.

616
00:51:56,379 --> 00:52:02,113
First line: NCAA, address...
I assume you have it, Luann.

617
00:52:02,285 --> 00:52:04,412
It's somewhere in Kansas City.

618
00:52:04,588 --> 00:52:08,524
Salutation: To whom it may concern.

619
00:52:09,593 --> 00:52:12,790
As I am sure you are aware, we...

620
00:52:13,763 --> 00:52:16,231
I'm gonna take a road trip
southeast of here...

621
00:52:16,399 --> 00:52:19,926
...and go get this Shaw kid
down in Martinsville.

622
00:52:20,103 --> 00:52:22,094
I'm gonna take a shot at Gibbs.

623
00:52:22,272 --> 00:52:24,502
Go get us a quarterback, coach.

624
00:52:39,322 --> 00:52:42,291
- Jake. Red Dawson.
- Yes, sir?

625
00:52:50,333 --> 00:52:53,700
I know coaches from quite a few schools
have already come to talk...

626
00:52:53,870 --> 00:52:57,829
...about your son playing football for them.
I hope that he hasn't made his mind up.

627
00:52:58,008 --> 00:52:59,839
Ain't no way he's made up his mind yet.

628
00:53:00,810 --> 00:53:03,005
Wait, there he is, right there.

629
00:53:14,357 --> 00:53:16,484
Oh, what's the good word, coach?

630
00:53:19,296 --> 00:53:21,321
No? Shit.

631
00:53:23,533 --> 00:53:26,366
Truman Andrews. Here we come.

632
00:53:50,493 --> 00:53:52,393
Shit.

633
00:53:53,797 --> 00:53:55,458
Luann?

634
00:53:59,135 --> 00:54:00,363
Sir?

635
00:54:00,537 --> 00:54:03,199
Has the NCAA returned
any of my calls yet?

636
00:54:03,373 --> 00:54:04,772
No.

637
00:54:07,277 --> 00:54:10,246
Six, seven, eight, nine, 10,
11 at West Virginia.

638
00:54:10,413 --> 00:54:14,873
Kids that we wanted who are now
in West Virginia. Who's that?

639
00:54:15,485 --> 00:54:17,817
Bob Lambert. West Virginia.

640
00:54:17,988 --> 00:54:19,478
Shit.

641
00:54:19,656 --> 00:54:21,089
Twelve. West Virginia.

642
00:54:21,258 --> 00:54:24,421
Red, we gotta broaden our
recruiting base or something.

643
00:54:24,594 --> 00:54:27,927
We gotta get creative about...

644
00:54:28,198 --> 00:54:31,065
...who we're going after,
where we're going after them...

645
00:54:31,234 --> 00:54:34,431
...and how we're going after them.
Isn't that right, doc?

646
00:54:36,172 --> 00:54:37,969
Good morning, Red.

647
00:54:39,409 --> 00:54:42,139
Well, how are we doing?

648
00:54:42,312 --> 00:54:44,337
West Virginia will be
competitive next year.

649
00:54:44,514 --> 00:54:46,880
Yeah, very.
How about you?

650
00:54:47,751 --> 00:54:53,815
Well, Jack, I haven't heard anything
positive back yet.

651
00:54:53,990 --> 00:54:56,481
And I think I've done everything I can.

652
00:54:56,793 --> 00:55:00,126
Maybe we need more time.
I don't know.

653
00:55:01,097 --> 00:55:04,191
Time's the only thing
we don't have, Don.

654
00:55:04,367 --> 00:55:10,829
I mean, hell, it's already April.
Time is not our friend.

655
00:55:14,477 --> 00:55:16,945
Let me ask you a question.
Now, are you married?

656
00:55:17,113 --> 00:55:18,876
Yes, I am. 25 years in May.

657
00:55:19,049 --> 00:55:22,280
Twenty-five years. I am willing to bet...

658
00:55:23,320 --> 00:55:26,585
...that you didn't propose over the phone.

659
00:55:29,125 --> 00:55:30,956
No, I didn't.

660
00:55:31,127 --> 00:55:36,793
Okay. And I know damn well
that she didn't say yes in a letter.

661
00:55:39,736 --> 00:55:41,328
- Jack?
- Doc?

662
00:55:41,504 --> 00:55:44,940
- No, Jack. I know...
- Yes. Doc?

663
00:55:45,108 --> 00:55:46,336
You can do it.

664
00:55:48,478 --> 00:55:50,503
You're an outlaw. Pioneer.

665
00:55:51,014 --> 00:55:54,381
Gunslinger.
This is a whole new game, doc.

666
00:55:56,986 --> 00:55:58,977
You...

667
00:55:59,389 --> 00:56:01,016
You.

668
00:56:01,524 --> 00:56:05,085
There's a first time for everything, Don.

669
00:56:06,596 --> 00:56:09,258
If we're gonna survive, this has
to be one of those times.

670
00:56:09,432 --> 00:56:11,900
And you're the only man that can do it.

671
00:56:22,846 --> 00:56:28,409
Excuse me, sir? Excuse me,
I'm sorry to bother you like this...

672
00:56:29,686 --> 00:56:33,417
...but my name is Don Dedmon,
I'm president of Marshall University.

673
00:56:33,990 --> 00:56:36,220
May I speak with you
for a moment, please?

674
00:56:37,327 --> 00:56:39,659
What are you doing in Kansas City, Don?

675
00:56:40,296 --> 00:56:44,665
My town, my school, we're hurting.

676
00:56:45,135 --> 00:56:50,129
We want to play football,
and we cannot do it without your help.

677
00:56:54,978 --> 00:56:56,536
Please.

678
00:57:16,433 --> 00:57:18,594
Guess who's going to change our diaper.

679
00:57:21,337 --> 00:57:24,431
Yeah!

680
00:57:24,607 --> 00:57:26,074
Get him!

681
00:57:26,242 --> 00:57:28,904
Need a little help here, Red.
He's heavier than you think.

682
00:57:29,078 --> 00:57:31,569
He's all wet.
He's all wet.

683
00:57:32,582 --> 00:57:34,072
Approved.

684
00:57:34,250 --> 00:57:38,243
"You will be allowed to play freshmen
at Marshall University."

685
00:57:38,421 --> 00:57:41,117
- What's that right there? What's that?
- Here, put me down.

686
00:57:41,291 --> 00:57:44,590
That is signed by the president right there.
There he is. Stamped.

687
00:57:44,761 --> 00:57:47,286
Doc, we're gonna get us a football team.

688
00:57:48,364 --> 00:57:51,128
And that is why we are offering
your son something...

689
00:57:51,301 --> 00:57:53,701
...that no other school in the country can.

690
00:57:53,970 --> 00:57:58,839
Immediate and substantial playing time
as a freshman.

691
00:58:14,157 --> 00:58:16,990
Time! I like the kid
who made the lay-up.

692
00:58:17,160 --> 00:58:20,618
This is the one I wanna talk to, right here.
What's your name, son?

693
00:58:25,235 --> 00:58:27,226
Ball, ball, ball!

694
00:58:32,008 --> 00:58:33,908
- That was a hell of a hit.
- Thank you.

695
00:58:34,077 --> 00:58:36,477
- Coach Dawson, from the football club.
- Bobby Jordan.

696
00:58:36,646 --> 00:58:38,910
- Ever play any football? None at all?
- No, sir.

697
00:58:39,082 --> 00:58:42,108
- No Pop Warner, no high school?
- No. Just baseball.

698
00:58:46,923 --> 00:58:48,857
Groovy. Come on, man.

699
00:58:49,259 --> 00:58:50,692
Hey, let me rap to you.

700
00:58:59,769 --> 00:59:01,327
Hey, how you doing?

701
00:59:03,973 --> 00:59:06,771
Hey. What's up, man?

702
00:59:20,623 --> 00:59:24,491
Strong finish.
That's a good-looking board.

703
00:59:25,795 --> 00:59:29,697
Good-looking board.
I'm tired of flying.

704
00:59:32,368 --> 00:59:37,305
Marshall Thundering Herd all-freshmen
team, led by quarterback John Cady...

705
00:59:38,975 --> 00:59:43,776
...handing the ball off
to the ever-talented Lucas Booth!

706
00:59:43,947 --> 00:59:46,677
He runs to the inside,
and who's on the outsider wing?

707
00:59:46,849 --> 00:59:49,647
Terry Gardner catches it,
pitches to Tennis Rice...

708
00:59:49,819 --> 00:59:53,311
...who's going downfield to
tight end Sam Boteck.

709
01:00:19,749 --> 01:00:20,977
I've never been.

710
01:00:21,150 --> 01:00:22,674
- Crazy. In four years?
- Yeah.

711
01:00:22,852 --> 01:00:24,217
- The bonfire.
- I've never been.

712
01:00:24,387 --> 01:00:26,378
- Everyone's been to the bonfire.
- I haven't.

713
01:00:26,556 --> 01:00:28,888
- Do you eat marshmallows?
- I love marshmallows.

714
01:00:29,058 --> 01:00:32,824
- You've gotta come to the bonfire.
- Annie, order's up.

715
01:00:33,930 --> 01:00:36,160
- Ask her to come.
- I will, I will.

716
01:00:40,536 --> 01:00:42,470
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

717
01:00:43,539 --> 01:00:46,838
- Can we have some silverware?
- Sure.

718
01:00:52,482 --> 01:00:55,076
- Some guys have all the luck.
- Sorry?

719
01:00:55,251 --> 01:00:57,845
Your fiancé. He's a lucky guy.

720
01:00:59,922 --> 01:01:03,824
- Can you drive? Yeah.
- Yeah. We'll leave about 8?

721
01:01:12,468 --> 01:01:15,835
Keith? It's your turn
to set the table!

722
01:01:16,005 --> 01:01:17,734
He's not here, Mom.

723
01:01:18,274 --> 01:01:20,572
- Where is he?
- I don't know.

724
01:01:22,412 --> 01:01:24,573
Okay, guys. First things first.

725
01:01:24,747 --> 01:01:26,977
Feel a connection to the guy next to you.

726
01:01:27,150 --> 01:01:30,119
Hand on a knee, hook an arm,
whatever it is.

727
01:01:30,520 --> 01:01:32,147
Come on, Herd.

728
01:01:32,321 --> 01:01:34,915
Look around, because these
are your teammates, young men.

729
01:01:35,091 --> 01:01:38,083
They're made up of three
returning varsity members.

730
01:01:38,261 --> 01:01:41,890
Randy Linden, George Olson, Nate Ruffin.

731
01:01:42,065 --> 01:01:46,058
Fifteen freshmen turning sophomores.

732
01:01:46,235 --> 01:01:48,829
And the rest of you, true freshmen...

733
01:01:49,005 --> 01:01:52,634
...very first time in college football
and walk-ons.

734
01:01:52,809 --> 01:01:55,175
Are you gonna play too, Tom?

735
01:01:56,379 --> 01:01:59,974
Remember, this is a game called football,
let's get to work. Let's go.

736
01:02:12,061 --> 01:02:14,461
We are going to be running
the Power I, gentlemen...

737
01:02:14,630 --> 01:02:16,723
...which obviously starts
with a quarterback.

738
01:02:16,899 --> 01:02:19,732
- Red, what are my choices?
- Dave Walsh.

739
01:02:19,902 --> 01:02:22,735
Solid athlete. Solid arm. Solid kid.

740
01:02:22,905 --> 01:02:24,372
Okay.

741
01:02:25,108 --> 01:02:26,632
Who else?

742
01:02:26,809 --> 01:02:31,405
- Jack, that's it.
- That's it, 10?

743
01:02:31,581 --> 01:02:32,809
That's it, coach.

744
01:02:32,982 --> 01:02:35,212
All right, guys.
Competition breeds improvement.

745
01:02:35,384 --> 01:02:39,081
Now, we need options here.
Let's look around, keep our eyes open.

746
01:02:39,255 --> 01:02:43,419
We need legs, hands and a decent arm.
Right there. Who's 86?

747
01:02:43,960 --> 01:02:47,259
That's Reggie Oliver.
Receiver from Alabama.

748
01:02:47,430 --> 01:02:50,228
Bear Bryant called me personally,
actually, to recommend him.

749
01:02:50,399 --> 01:02:53,664
- You wanna try him out at QB?
- Unless you think it's a bad idea.

750
01:02:54,036 --> 01:02:57,005
- Let's push them to the limit, men, huh?
- Right, coach.

751
01:03:03,579 --> 01:03:05,513
Come on, hit it, now!

752
01:03:07,116 --> 01:03:08,447
Check!

753
01:03:17,160 --> 01:03:18,286
Not good, coach.

754
01:03:33,309 --> 01:03:35,470
James, James. Get over here.

755
01:03:37,513 --> 01:03:39,174
That's supposed to be a post route.

756
01:03:39,348 --> 01:03:41,111
- Post?
- Post.

757
01:03:41,284 --> 01:03:44,310
You do know the difference between a
post route and a flag route?

758
01:03:44,487 --> 01:03:45,715
No, coach.

759
01:03:45,888 --> 01:03:49,346
All right, all right.
You see the big goalpost there?

760
01:03:49,525 --> 01:03:53,256
That's why they call it a post route. Post.
You head right to that post.

761
01:03:53,429 --> 01:03:55,124
Cut 10 yards, to the post.

762
01:03:55,298 --> 01:03:57,766
See the big pylon down
at the corner of the end zone?

763
01:03:57,934 --> 01:03:59,697
That's what we call a flag, all right?

764
01:03:59,869 --> 01:04:01,734
So when you're running the flag route...

765
01:04:01,904 --> 01:04:04,429
...10 yards to the corner of the end zone,
to the flag.

766
01:04:04,607 --> 01:04:06,438
- All right? All right.
- I got it.

767
01:04:06,609 --> 01:04:08,304
Do it again.

768
01:04:18,855 --> 01:04:21,255
Come on! Let's go!

769
01:04:21,791 --> 01:04:24,453
Nice speed, Booth! Nice speed!

770
01:04:26,128 --> 01:04:28,596
Nice speed. Shalhoop. Hey.

771
01:04:28,764 --> 01:04:31,824
- What are you doing?
- Oh, I kick the ball, coach.

772
01:04:32,001 --> 01:04:34,799
But after you kick it, son,
you're still a football player.

773
01:04:41,377 --> 01:04:44,039
Good job, George. Good job, George.
Come here, come here.

774
01:04:44,213 --> 01:04:46,078
- What's your name, 51?
- My name's Creole.

775
01:04:46,249 --> 01:04:48,274
Creole. This Redbook's
taking me only so far.

776
01:04:48,451 --> 01:04:52,478
Urbanek, I need names. Last names on
everyone's helmet. All right? This afternoon.

777
01:04:52,655 --> 01:04:56,614
Now, Creole, the man outweighs you
by 75 pounds. Okay?

778
01:04:56,792 --> 01:04:58,384
When you're hitting him up high...

779
01:04:58,561 --> 01:05:01,587
...he'll beat you and you'll be
on your ass every time, all right?

780
01:05:01,764 --> 01:05:03,925
You gotta come in here,
you gotta get him low.

781
01:05:04,100 --> 01:05:07,558
Get him in the legs, okay? That's how
you'll keep him from coming through.

782
01:05:07,737 --> 01:05:10,535
- Stay low on him. Low, man.
- What should I do if he goes low?

783
01:05:10,706 --> 01:05:13,368
Good question. George says,
what does he do if he goes low?

784
01:05:13,542 --> 01:05:15,942
Five-one comes low.
Head slap and you're around him.

785
01:05:16,112 --> 01:05:18,774
Like that. You see that?
Head-slap the shit out of him.

786
01:05:29,759 --> 01:05:33,820
- Give me second team, McNally.
- We don't have a second team, Jack.

787
01:05:33,996 --> 01:05:37,762
Shit. Okay, yeah, we do
have a second team. Jackson! Urbanek!

788
01:05:37,934 --> 01:05:39,925
Lengyel, McNally, Dawson...

789
01:05:40,102 --> 01:05:42,263
...line up here.
Offensive line, watch this.

790
01:05:42,438 --> 01:05:45,635
- Coach, you don't have any pads on.
- Now, you just play ball, Olson.

791
01:05:47,777 --> 01:05:49,142
Quarterback's still standing.

792
01:05:49,312 --> 01:05:51,439
Big on big.
We can run an offense.

793
01:05:51,614 --> 01:05:55,846
We can save a young man's life.
Come on, now. Power I. Big on big.

794
01:06:01,257 --> 01:06:04,192
We got a huge problem
on the O-line, coach.

795
01:06:05,227 --> 01:06:08,162
I don't think it's because
the defensive line is so spectacular.

796
01:06:08,331 --> 01:06:09,662
No. No.

797
01:06:11,133 --> 01:06:15,797
Men. Power I. You know I'm a fan
of it, that's why I brought it here.

798
01:06:15,972 --> 01:06:18,805
I have learned in the last two weeks
that it is not working.

799
01:06:18,975 --> 01:06:22,570
So as of right now, the Power I
goes in the trash...

800
01:06:22,745 --> 01:06:27,079
...along with every flea-flicker,
double reverse...

801
01:06:27,249 --> 01:06:30,241
...and every other trick play
that you may have in your playbook.

802
01:06:30,419 --> 01:06:33,820
Get rid of it.
Men, it is time to simplify. Ball.

803
01:06:34,957 --> 01:06:37,323
So put our heads together here.

804
01:06:37,493 --> 01:06:39,654
What is the simplest offense...

805
01:06:41,731 --> 01:06:44,564
...that you have ever run
and actually won a football game?

806
01:06:44,734 --> 01:06:49,068
Any idea's a good idea. No right or wrong
in here today, men, let's talk it out.

807
01:06:49,238 --> 01:06:50,603
Well, there's always the Veer.

808
01:06:50,773 --> 01:06:54,641
The Veer. That's interesting.
Talk that out, Red.

809
01:06:55,244 --> 01:06:59,305
Well, the Veer's an option offense.
Spreads things out.

810
01:06:59,482 --> 01:07:01,074
Takes the focus off any one man.

811
01:07:01,250 --> 01:07:04,185
It's designed for teams that don't
have a strong offensive line.

812
01:07:04,653 --> 01:07:08,111
Now, that is us in a nutshell.
Well, who runs it that we can talk to?

813
01:07:08,290 --> 01:07:10,690
Bill Yeoman came up with it
at Houston...

814
01:07:10,860 --> 01:07:14,193
...but other than West Virginia,
no one really runs it outside of Texas.

815
01:07:16,298 --> 01:07:18,823
- West Virginia runs the Veer?
- Yeah.

816
01:07:24,073 --> 01:07:28,442
Jack, that's crazy. We're rivals.

817
01:07:28,611 --> 01:07:31,705
You think they'll invite us to lunch
and hand over their playbook?

818
01:07:31,881 --> 01:07:33,781
They don't have to take us out to lunch.

819
01:07:33,949 --> 01:07:36,008
We'll pick some up on the way.

820
01:07:36,385 --> 01:07:40,685
Morgantown. The Veer. I like it.

821
01:07:45,027 --> 01:07:48,258
Eight-time Southern
Conference Champions, Red.

822
01:07:48,431 --> 01:07:52,697
Jack? Jack, I gotta tell you,
I really don't think this is your best idea.

823
01:07:53,035 --> 01:07:56,334
- Red! Good to see you again.
- Oh, coach.

824
01:07:56,505 --> 01:07:58,666
- How are you?
- How are you?

825
01:07:58,841 --> 01:08:00,900
- And this must be?
- Coach Jack Lengyel.

826
01:08:01,077 --> 01:08:03,477
Jack. Bobby Bowden.
Pleasure to meet you.

827
01:08:03,646 --> 01:08:05,273
It's a pleasure to meet you.

828
01:08:05,448 --> 01:08:07,814
Bobby, thank you for taking
the time with us today.

829
01:08:07,983 --> 01:08:10,349
- My pleasure, not a problem.
- All right.

830
01:08:10,519 --> 01:08:12,077
Yes, sir.

831
01:08:12,588 --> 01:08:15,955
So I can't wait to hear.
What can I do for you boys?

832
01:08:17,660 --> 01:08:19,525
Well, the thing is...

833
01:08:20,563 --> 01:08:21,996
...coach...

834
01:08:22,565 --> 01:08:26,501
...we're thinking about adopting
the Veer this year.

835
01:08:26,735 --> 01:08:29,795
Now, I understand that to be
your bread and butter, as it were.

836
01:08:29,972 --> 01:08:32,668
We're just hoping that we could
come down here and maybe...

837
01:08:32,842 --> 01:08:34,810
...you could give us a few pointers.

838
01:08:41,851 --> 01:08:43,113
- Pointers?
- Tips.

839
01:08:43,285 --> 01:08:47,051
Advice. Anything that you'd
be willing to show us.

840
01:08:47,389 --> 01:08:52,588
Well, we'd really appreciate it. You seem
to be the man who runs it so well.

841
01:08:55,264 --> 01:08:56,595
He's good.

842
01:08:59,135 --> 01:09:01,626
- You're the best at the Veer.
- That's what they say!

843
01:09:01,804 --> 01:09:03,738
I'm coming straight to the man.

844
01:09:08,410 --> 01:09:10,344
Reg, I got your burger.

845
01:09:10,513 --> 01:09:13,243
- Chili on the fries?
- They were out.

846
01:09:13,415 --> 01:09:17,408
Come on, Stretch. Gonna be a rough year
if that's the best you can do.

847
01:09:28,230 --> 01:09:29,822
What?

